OL,3,CRevealed: The billions needed to plug
OL,4,CStormont funding gaps
OL,6,FThe Stormont powersharing Executive
OL,7,Fwas restored in February. The UK
OL,8,FGovernment agreed a #3.3 billion
OL,9,Fpackage to support the return of
OL,10,Fdevolution.JThe new Executive agreed a
OL,11,Fshort delay in setting a budget for
OL,12,F2024/25 while ministers got to grip
OL,13,Fwith their departmental priorities.JMs
OL,14,FArchibald has been meeting with
OL,15,Fministers ahead of introducing a final
OL,16,Fbudget paper to the Executive. The
OL,17,Fbudget is expected to be brought to
OL,18,Fthe Assembly before the end of April.
OL,19,FDemand on the budget far outstrips the
OL,20,Ffunding available.
